President Obama reflects on the 70th Anniversary of the GI Bill in an op-ed published in Military Times. He discusses how the GI Bill has helped veterans and their families by providing education and skills training, and how it has transformed America by sparking careers and contributing to the growth of the middle class. President Obama emphasizes the importance of the Post-9/11 GI Bill in supporting veterans' education, and encourages eligible individuals to take advantage of the benefits it offers. He also highlights the need for schools to adhere to the Principles of Excellence and foster an environment that supports veterans. Additionally, President Obama discusses efforts to make college more affordable and protect students from excessive debt, as well as initiatives to help veterans transition into civilian jobs. He concludes by reaffirming the commitment to support veterans and ensure that the investments made in them today will produce the leaders America needs in the future.